						<summary>

						<p>Rock to the north of the base-relief of Jaina images in Pēchchippaḷḷam Samaṇarmalai hill near the stone lamp post.</p>						

						<p>12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription mentions the Jaina teachers Āriyadēva, Baḷachandradēva of Beḷaguḷa, who belonged to the Mūla-saṁgha, Nēmidēva, Ajitasēnadēva and Gōvardhanadēva. The characters are of about 12th century A.D. </p>						

						</summary>
